Rules_Report.message: One or more of the window attributes (windowLabel, windowLower, windowUpper) is missing.

The Timing type is "Fixed Reference" (type.code=C201358) but it does not point to only one scheduled instance - relativeToScheduledInstanceId is not missing and does not contain the same value as relativeFromScheduledInstanceId.
The defaultConditionId and timelineExitId attributes are either both populated or both empty.
A required biomedical concept property (isRequired=true) is not enabled (isEnabled is not true), or a disabled biomedical concept property (isEnabled=false) is required (isRequired is not false).
Population of otherReason is not consistent with code - code.code is C17649 ('Other') but otherReason is blank, or otherReason is present but code.code is not C17649 ('Other').
An instance of a class is referencing itself as its previous instance.

The next and previous relationships are not reciprocal - the instance is the "previous" instance (parent_rel is "previousId") for an instance that is not its "next" instance (nextId is not the same as parent_id), or vice versa.
One or more of the window attributes (windowLabel, windowLower, windowUpper) contains a value for a Fixed Reference timing (type.code=C201358).
The same instance is referenced more than once as previous or next - nextId or previousId values are not unique.

The Timing type is not "Fixed Reference" (type.code is not C201358) but it does not point to two different scheduled instances - relativeFromScheduledInstanceId and/or relativeToScheduledInstanceId is missing, or they both contain the same value.
The business therapeutic areas of the study version are not unique - the same code is used more than once with the same codeSystem and codeSystemVersion.
There is not a one-to-one relationship between code and decode within a codeSytem and corresponding codeSystemVersion
Type is "Fixed Reference" (type.code=C201358) for the timing but relativeToFrom is not "Start to Start" (relativeToFrom.code is not C201355).
The study element is not referenced by any study cell.

The relative to/from scheduled instance of a timing was not defined within the same timeline as the timing: the parent_id of the scheduled instance ($parent_of_scheduled_instance) is not the same as parent_id of the timing (parent_id.Timing).
The planned age range is marked as approximate, which is not expected.
The unit for a subject enrollement quantity is not empty or coded as % (codeSystem = http://www.cdisc.org, code = C25613 and decode = %).
The schedule timeline does not have a defined exit: none of its scheduled activity instances has a timeline exit.

The study element is referenced by a study cell but was not defined within the same study design as the study cell: the parent_id of the study element ($parent_of_study_element) is not the same as parent_id of the study cell (parent_id.StudyCell).
The biomedical concept category is referenced more than once from the same activity.
The biomedical concept category does not have any members or children.
The standard code aliases of the alias code are not unique - the same code is used more than once with the same codeSystem and codeSystemVersion.
The study version has a type of governance date with a global geographic scope and either another date of the same type or additional geographic scope(s) defined for the date.
Planned age has not been specified for either the study population or the cohort, or it has been specified for both.
The epoch is not referenced by any scheduled activity instances.
There is more than one title of the same type code or decode.
The scheduled activity instance is referencing its parent timeline as its sub-timeline.
The scheduled activity instance references a timeline exit that is not defined within the same schedule timeline as the scheduled activity instance.
The value attribute of the timing is not a non-negative duration in ISO 8601 format.
The condition assignment's target is the same as its parent.
There is no exit defined for the timeline.
The study version does not have a title of type "Official Study Title" (type.code = C207616 or type.decode = "Official Study Title", both case insensitive).
A scheduled activity/decision instance is referencing itself as its default condition.
The lower limit of the timing window (windowLower) is not a non-negative duration in ISO 8601 format.
The upper limit of the timing window (windowUpper) is not a non-negative duration in ISO 8601 format.

The encounter is scheduled at a timing that either is not defined in the same study design (the parent_id of the timing's parent schedule timeline does not match the parent_id of the encounter) or is invalid (schedulateAtId does not match the id of any timing).

The standard code alias is the same as the standard code - the same combination of code system, code system version and either code or decode is used for both the standard code and the standard code alias (case insensitive).
The contact modes of the encounter are not unique - the same code is used more than once with the same codeSystem and codeSystemVersion.

The timing has a type of "Fixed Reference" (type.code=C201358) but it is not related to a scheduled activity instance via a relativeFromScheduledInstance relationship - the value of relativeFromScheduledInstanceId is missing or it does not match the id value of a ScheduledActivityInstance.
The codes of the indication are not unique - the same code is used more than once with the same codeSystem and codeSystemVersion.
The codes of the study intervention are not unique - the same code is used more than once with the same codeSystem and codeSystemVersion.
The reference is not a fixed value (it contains "usdm:ref") but it is not specified in the correct format.
The governance date has more than one geographic scope defined, at least one of which has type of "Global" (type.code = C68846 or type.decode = "Global", both case insensitive).
The study cell references an arm that is not defined within the same study design as the study cell.
The study cell references an epoch that is not defined within the same study design as the study cell.
The activity references a previous or next activity that is not specified within the same study design.
The encounter references a previous or next encounter that is not specified within the same study design.
The epoch references a previous or next epoch that is not specified within the same study design.
The activity references a timeline that is not specified within the same study design.
An instance of a class is referencing itself as its next instance.
An instance of a class is being referenced as one of its own children.

The eligibility criterion's category is not specified using the Category of Inclusion/Exclusion (C66797) SDTM codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive), and/or neither code nor decode is found in the codelist.

The study intervention's type is not specified using the Intervention Type Response (C99078) SDTM codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive), and/or neither code nor decode is found in the codelist.

The encounter's contact mode is not specified according to the extensible Mode of Subject Contact (C171445) SDTM codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, and/or the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive).

The planned sex is not specified using the Sex of Participants (C66732) SDTM codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive), and/or neither code nor decode is found in the codelist.

The encounter's environmental setting is not specified according to the extensible Environmental Setting (C127262) SDTM codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, and/or the code or decode is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive).
The schedule timeline does not contain an anchor (i.e., a scheduled activity instance that is referenced by a Fixed Reference timing).
The duration will vary (durationWillVary is not 'false' or reasonDurationWillVary is populated), but it is not fully defined (durationWillVary is not 'true' or reasonDurationWillVary is missing).
The scheduled activity instance is in the main timeline but does not refer to an epoch.
The study version has more than one governance date with the same type and geographic scope.
The primary endpoint (level.code = C94496) is not referenced by a primary objective (level.code.Objective = C85826).
Planned sex has not been specified for either the study population or the cohort, or it has been specified for both.
The scheduled activity instance has a sub-timeline that is not defined within the same study design.

The specified context of the condition is not a valid instance of either the Activity or ScheduledActivityInstance class (the value of the condition's contextIds attribute either matches the id of an instance that is not an Activity or ScheduledActivityInstance, or it does not match the id of any class instance).
The code system is "http://www.cdisc.org" but the code system version is not a valid CDISC terminology release date in ISO 8601 date format.
The environmental settings of the encounter are not unique - the same code is used more than once with the same codeSystem and codeSystemVersion.

The timing's type is not specified using the Timing Type Value Set Terminology (C201264) DDF codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive), and/or neither code nor decode is found in the codelist.

The timing's relative to/from property is not specified using the Timing Relative To From Value Set Terminology (C201265) DDF codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive), and/or neither code nor decode is found in the codelist.

The study intervention's role is not specified using the study intervention role (C207417) DDF codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive), and/or neither code nor decode is found in the codelist.

The governance date type is not specified according to the extensible governance date type (C207413) DDF codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, and/or the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive).

The study amendment reason is not coded using the study amendment reason (C207415) DDF codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, and/or the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive).

The study geographic scope type is not specified using the geographic scope type (C207412) DDF codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive), and/or neither code nor decode is found in the codelist.

The study title type is not specified using the study title type (C207419) DDF codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive), and/or neither code nor decode is found in the codelist.
The datatype of the attribute does not conform with the USDM schema.
Attributes are not included as defined in the USDM schema - required properties are missing or additional properties are present.

The cardinality of the attribute is not as defined in the USDM schema - the attribute is required but does not have a value (the value is too short), or the attribute is a list and has either too few entries (the list is too short) or too many entries (the list is too long).

The objective level is not specified using the objective level (C188725) DDF codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive), and/or neither code nor decode is found in the codelist.

The endpoint level is not specified using the endpoint level (C188726) DDF codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive), and/or neither code nor decode is found in the codelist.

The study arm data origin type is not specified according to the extensible data origin type (C188727) DDF codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, and/or the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive).

The encounter type is not specified according to the extensible encounter type (C188728) DDF codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, and/or the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive).

The study definition document type is not specified according to the extensible study definition document type (C215477) DDF codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, and/or the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive).
The reference to the narrative content item is not targetting a narrative content item that has been defined within the study.
The text attribute contains non-conformant XHTML.
The combination of arm and epoch occurs more than once within the study design.
The class relationship does not conform with the USDM schema.
The scheduled activity/decision instance references an epoch that is not defined within the same study design.

The study definition document version's status is not specified using the status Value Set Terminology (C188723) DDF codelist - codeSystem is not "http://www.cdisc.org", codeSystemVersion is not a valid terminology package date, the code or decode (either as preferred term or as submission value) is found in the codelist (case insensitive) but the corresponding decode or code does not match the codelist value (case sensitive), and/or neither code nor decode is found in the codelist.
